Great customer service here.  They measured my son for his first road bike and really took the time to get the right size and style. Their staff are patient and knowledgable.

In addition they have nice benefits with a bike purchase including a free tune up, free adjustments for two years, and a guaranteed trade in value if you want to upgrade within two years.  

In addition, their prices were at or better than the other bike shops in town.

The food is good but the wait for food can be long, even for late night dining.
The pig's foot with foie gras is rich, over the top, and very delicious. The seafood platter was also quite good though a lot of it was sauced heavily. Great wine list, ask for recommendations.

Tons of samples in the produce section. The oranges and cherry tomatoes are some kind of delicious. They sprinkle a little salt on the tomatoes to bring out the sweetness. Genius.

There's a vendor outside with Maple Syrup products who also sells cold fresh made cranberry juice. So refreshing in hot weather.

Drinks- Poseidon (a Bloody Caesar made w\/ soy, housemade habanero & pickles w\/ a freshly shucked oyster on top) and Canadian Hunter (No3 gin martini, spruce tips, & laphroaig rinse).
The Beef Tartare is made w\/ organic grass fed dry aged beef from Scotch Mountain Meats and is probably the best beef tartare I've ever had anywhere.
Locally sourced seasonal ingredients. Farm to Table dining at its very best. Some of the best food to be had in the city.

The sides on the a la carte menu are all quite large so be prepared. The vegetable side comes with roasted butternut squash, beets, Jerusalem artichoke, and sautéed Swiss chard. All very very good. (12\/31\/12)
The Steak Hache is essentially a seared steak tartare with a fried egg on top. Really really good stuff. Come w\/ some roasted veg and fries.
One of three locations in the city. Cool little spot for coffee. Both the latte and cappuccino are quite good.

Hearty and delicious fillings sandwiched in between corn cakes. A bit messy but so so good. Watch out for the red sauce- it's made w\/ scotch bonnet peppers and a little goes a long way. The Carne Mechada (slow cooked and shredded beef) is great. Really friendly service.
Nice cozy spot to get coffee. Decent latte.
The T Rex is a thing of meaty goodness- Fries topped w\/ ground beef, hot dogs, smoked sausage, bacon, gravy, & cheese curds. So. Good.
